Detailed Description

The hyperdbg command interpreter and driver connector.

45 {
46  UINT64 TargetPid = 0;
47  BOOLEAN NextIsPid = FALSE;
48 
49  //
50  // Disable user-mode debugger in this version
51  //
52 #if ActivateUserModeDebugger == FALSE
53 
54  if (!g_IsSerialConnectedToRemoteDebugger)
55  {
56  ShowMessages("The user-mode debugger is still in the beta version and not stable. "
57  "We decided to exclude it from this release and release it in future versions. "
58  "If you want to test the user-mode debugger in VMI Mode, you should build "
59  "HyperDbg with special instructions. \nPlease follow the steps here: "
60  "https://docs.hyperdbg.org/getting-started/build-and-install \n");
61  return;
62  }
63 
64 #endif // !ActivateUserModeDebugger
65 
66  //
67  // It's a attach to a target PID
68  //
69  if (SplittedCommand.size() >= 4)
70  {
71  ShowMessages("incorrect use of '.attach'\n\n");
72  CommandAttachHelp();
73  return;
74  }
75 
76  //
77  // .attach and .detach commands are only supported in VMI Mode
78  //
79  if (g_IsSerialConnectedToRemoteDebuggee)
80  {
81  ShowMessages("err, '.attach', and '.detach' commands are only usable "
82  "in VMI Mode, you can use the '.process', or the '.thread' "
83  "in Debugger Mode\n");
84  return;
85  }
86 
87  for (auto item : SplittedCommand)
88  {
89  //
90  // Find out whether the user enters pid or not
91  //
92  if (NextIsPid)
93  {
94  NextIsPid = FALSE;
95 
96  if (!ConvertStringToUInt64(item, &TargetPid))
97  {
98  ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex value for process id\n\n");
99  CommandAttachHelp();
100  return;
101  }
102  }
103  else if (!item.compare("pid"))
104  {
105  //
106  // next item is a pid for the process
107  //
108  NextIsPid = TRUE;
109  }
110  }
111 
112  //
113  // Check if the process id is empty or not
114  //
115  if (TargetPid == 0)
116  {
117  ShowMessages("please specify a hex value for process id\n\n");
118  CommandAttachHelp();
119  return;
120  }
121 
122  //
123  // Perform attach to target process
124  //
125  UdAttachToProcess(TargetPid, NULL, NULL);
126 }

56  return;

58 
59  //
60  // Get the breakpoint id
61  //

65  CommandBcHelp();
66 
67  return;
68  }
69 
70  //
71  // Check if the remote serial debuggee is paused or not (connected or not)
72  //

74  {
75  //
76  // Perform clearing breakpoint
77  //
78  Request.Request = DEBUGGEE_BREAKPOINT_MODIFICATION_REQUEST_CLEAR;

81  // Set breakpoint id
82  //
83  Request.BreakpointId = BreakpointId;
84 
85  //
86  // Send the request
87  //
88  KdSendListOrModifyPacketToDebuggee(&Request);
89  }
90  else

92  ShowMessages("err, clearing breakpoints is only valid if you connected to "

205  // Everything is okay, connect to the remote machine to send (debugger)
206  //
207  KdPrepareAndConnectDebugPort(SplittedCommand.at(4).c_str(), Baudrate, Port, FALSE, FALSE);
208  }
209  else if (!SplittedCommand.at(2).compare("namedpipe"))
210  {
211  //
212  // Connect to a remote namedpipe
213  //
214  string Delimiter = "namedpipe";
215  string Token = Command.substr(
216  Command.find(Delimiter) + Delimiter.size() + 1,
217  Command.size());
218 
219  //
220  // Connect to a namedpipe (it's probably a Virtual Machine debugging)
221  //
222  KdPrepareAndConnectDebugPort(Token.c_str(), NULL, NULL, FALSE, TRUE);
223  }
224  else
225  {
226  //
227  // Unkonwn parameter
228  //
229  ShowMessages("unknown parameter '%s'\n\n", SplittedCommand.at(2).c_str());
230  CommandDebugHelp();
231  return;
232  }
233  }
234  else if (!SplittedCommand.at(1).compare("prepare"))
235  {
236  if (SplittedCommand.size() != 5)
237  {
238  ShowMessages("incorrect use of '.debug'\n\n");
239  CommandDebugHelp();
240  return;
241  }
242 
243  //
244  // in the case of 'prepare'
245  // currently we only support serial
246  //
247  if (!SplittedCommand.at(2).compare("serial"))
248  {
249  //
250  // Set baudrate
251  //
252  if (!IsNumber(SplittedCommand.at(3)))
253  {
254  //
255  // Unkonwn parameter
256  //
257  ShowMessages("unknown parameter '%s'\n\n",
258  SplittedCommand.at(3).c_str());
259  CommandDebugHelp();
260  return;
261  }
262 
263  Baudrate = stoi(SplittedCommand.at(3));
264 
265  //
266  // Check if baudrate is valid or not
267  //
268  if (!CommandDebugCheckBaudrate(Baudrate))
269  {
270  //
271  // Baud-rate is invalid
272  //
273  ShowMessages("err, baud rate is invalid\n\n");
274  CommandDebugHelp();
275  return;
276  }
277 
278  //
279  // check if com port address is valid or not
280  //
281  if (!CommandDebugCheckComPort(SplittedCommand.at(4), &Port))
282  {
283  //
284  // com port is invalid
285  //
286  ShowMessages("err, COM port is invalid\n\n");
287  CommandDebugHelp();
288  return;
289  }
290 
291  //
292  // Everything is okay, prepare to send (debuggee)
293  //
294  KdPrepareAndConnectDebugPort(SplittedCommand.at(4).c_str(), Baudrate, Port, TRUE, FALSE);
295  }
296  else
297  {
298  ShowMessages("invalid parameter '%s'\n\n", SplittedCommand.at(2));
299  CommandDebugHelp();
300  return;
301  }
302  }
303  else
304  {
305  ShowMessages("invalid parameter '%s'\n\n", SplittedCommand.at(1));
306  CommandDebugHelp();
307  return;
308  }
309 }

VOID CommandEditMemory ( vector< string >  SplittedCommand,

)

!e* and e* commands handler

60 {
61  BOOL Status;
62  UINT64 Address;
63  UINT64 * FinalBuffer;
64  vector<UINT64> ValuesToEdit;
65  BOOL SetAddress = FALSE;
66  BOOL SetValue = FALSE;
67  BOOL SetProcId = FALSE;
68  BOOL NextIsProcId = FALSE;
69  DEBUGGER_EDIT_MEMORY EditMemoryRequest = {0};
70  UINT64 Value = 0;
71  UINT32 ProcId = 0;
72  UINT32 CountOfValues = 0;
73  UINT32 FinalSize = 0;
74  vector<string> SplittedCommandCaseSensitive {Split(Command, ' ')};
75  UINT32 IndexInCommandCaseSensitive = 0;
76 
77  //
78  // By default if the user-debugger is active, we use these commands
79  // on the memory layout of the debuggee process
80  //
81  if (g_ActiveProcessDebuggingState.IsActive)
82  {
83  ProcId = g_ActiveProcessDebuggingState.ProcessId;
84  }
85 
86  if (SplittedCommand.size() <= 2)
87  {
88  ShowMessages("incorrect use of 'e*'\n\n");
89  CommandEditMemoryHelp();
90  return;
91  }
92 
93  for (auto Section : SplittedCommand)
94  {
95  IndexInCommandCaseSensitive++;
96 
97  if (!Section.compare(SplittedCommand.at(0)))
98  {
99  if (!Section.compare("!eb"))
100  {
101  EditMemoryRequest.MemoryType = EDIT_PHYSICAL_MEMORY;
102  EditMemoryRequest.ByteSize = EDIT_BYTE;
103  }
104  else if (!Section.compare("!ed"))
105  {
106  EditMemoryRequest.MemoryType = EDIT_PHYSICAL_MEMORY;
107  EditMemoryRequest.ByteSize = EDIT_DWORD;
108  }
109  else if (!Section.compare("!eq"))
110  {
111  EditMemoryRequest.MemoryType = EDIT_PHYSICAL_MEMORY;
112  EditMemoryRequest.ByteSize = EDIT_QWORD;
113  }
114  else if (!Section.compare("eb"))
115  {
116  EditMemoryRequest.MemoryType = EDIT_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
117  EditMemoryRequest.ByteSize = EDIT_BYTE;
118  }
119  else if (!Section.compare("ed"))
120  {
121  EditMemoryRequest.MemoryType = EDIT_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
122  EditMemoryRequest.ByteSize = EDIT_DWORD;
123  }
124  else if (!Section.compare("eq"))
125  {
126  EditMemoryRequest.MemoryType = EDIT_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
127  EditMemoryRequest.ByteSize = EDIT_QWORD;
128  }
129  else
130  {
131  //
132  // What's this? :(
133  //
134  ShowMessages("unknown error happened !\n\n");
135  CommandEditMemoryHelp();
136  return;
137  }
138 
139  continue;
140  }
141  if (NextIsProcId)
142  {
143  //
144  // It's a process id
145  //
146  NextIsProcId = FALSE;
147 
148  if (!ConvertStringToUInt32(Section, &ProcId))
149  {
150  ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex prcoess id\n\n");
151  CommandEditMemoryHelp();
152  return;
153  }
154  else
155  {
156  //
157  // Means that the proc id is set, next we should read value
158  //
159  continue;
160  }
161  }
162 
163  //
164  // Check if it's a process id or not
165  //
166  if (!SetProcId && !Section.compare("pid"))
167  {
168  NextIsProcId = TRUE;
169  continue;
170  }
171 
172  if (!SetAddress)
173  {
174  if (!SymbolConvertNameOrExprToAddress(SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(IndexInCommandCaseSensitive - 1),
175  &Address))
176  {
177  ShowMessages("err, couldn't resolve error at '%s'\n\n",
178  SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(IndexInCommandCaseSensitive - 1).c_str());
179  CommandEditMemoryHelp();
180  return;
181  }
182  else
183  {
184  //
185  // Means that the address is set, next we should read value
186  //
187  SetAddress = TRUE;
188  continue;
189  }
190  }
191 
192  if (SetAddress)
193  {
194  //
195  // Remove the hex notations
196  //
197  if (Section.rfind("0x", 0) == 0 || Section.rfind("0X", 0) == 0 ||
198  Section.rfind("\\x", 0) == 0 || Section.rfind("\\X", 0) == 0)
199  {
200  Section = Section.erase(0, 2);
201  }
202  else if (Section.rfind('x', 0) == 0 || Section.rfind('X', 0) == 0)
203  {
204  Section = Section.erase(0, 1);
205  }
206  Section.erase(remove(Section.begin(), Section.end(), '`'), Section.end());
207 
208  //
209  // Check if the value is valid based on byte counts
210  //
211  if (EditMemoryRequest.ByteSize == EDIT_BYTE && Section.size() >= 3)
212  {
213  ShowMessages("please specify a byte (hex) value for 'eb' or '!eb'\n\n");
214  return;
215  }
216  if (EditMemoryRequest.ByteSize == EDIT_DWORD && Section.size() >= 9)
217  {
218  ShowMessages(
219  "please specify a dword (hex) value for 'ed' or '!ed'\n\n");
220  return;
221  }
222  if (EditMemoryRequest.ByteSize == EDIT_QWORD && Section.size() >= 17)
223  {
224  ShowMessages(
225  "please specify a qword (hex) value for 'eq' or '!eq'\n\n");
226  return;
227  }
228 
229  //
230  // Qword is checked by the following function, no need to double
231  // check it above.
232  //
233 
234  if (!ConvertStringToUInt64(Section, &Value))
235  {
236  ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex value to change the memory "
237  "content\n\n");
238  CommandEditMemoryHelp();
239  return;
240  }
241  else
242  {
243  //
244  // Add it to the list
245  //
246 
247  ValuesToEdit.push_back(Value);
248 
249  //
250  // Keep track of values to modify
251  //
252  CountOfValues++;
253 
254  if (!SetValue)
255  {
256  //
257  // At least on value is there
258  //
259  SetValue = TRUE;
260  }
261  continue;
262  }
263  }
264  }
265 
266  //
267  // Check to prevent using process id in e* commands
268  //
269  if (g_IsSerialConnectedToRemoteDebuggee && ProcId != 0)
270  {
271  ShowMessages("err, you cannot specify 'pid' in the debugger mode\n\n");
272  return;
273  }
274 
275  if (ProcId == 0)
276  {
277  ProcId = GetCurrentProcessId();
278  }
279 
280  //
281  // Fill the structure
282  //
283  EditMemoryRequest.ProcessId = ProcId;
284  EditMemoryRequest.Address = Address;
285  EditMemoryRequest.CountOf64Chunks = CountOfValues;
286 
287  //
288  // Check if address and value are set or not
289  //
290  if (!SetAddress)
291  {
292  ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex address\n\n");
293  CommandEditMemoryHelp();
294  return;
295  }
296  if (!SetValue)
297  {
298  ShowMessages(
299  "please specify a correct hex value as the content to edit\n\n");
300  CommandEditMemoryHelp();
301  return;
302  }
303  if (NextIsProcId)
304  {
305  ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex value as the process id\n\n");
306  CommandEditMemoryHelp();
307  return;
308  }
309 
310  //
311  // Now it's time to put everything together in one structure
312  //
313  FinalSize = (CountOfValues * sizeof(UINT64)) + SIZEOF_DEBUGGER_EDIT_MEMORY;
314 
315  //
316  // Set the size
317  //
318  EditMemoryRequest.FinalStructureSize = FinalSize;
319 
320  //
321  // Allocate structure + buffer
322  //
323  FinalBuffer = (UINT64 *)malloc(FinalSize);
324 
325  if (!FinalBuffer)
326  {
327  ShowMessages("unable to allocate memory\n\n");
328  return;
329  }
330 
331  //
332  // Zero the buffer
333  //
334  ZeroMemory(FinalBuffer, FinalSize);
335 
336  //
337  // Copy the structure on top of the allocated buffer
338  //
339  memcpy(FinalBuffer, &EditMemoryRequest, SIZEOF_DEBUGGER_EDIT_MEMORY);
340 
341  //
342  // Put the values in 64 bit structures
343  //
344  std::copy(ValuesToEdit.begin(), ValuesToEdit.end(), (UINT64 *)((UINT64)FinalBuffer + SIZEOF_DEBUGGER_EDIT_MEMORY));
345 
346  //
347  // send the request
348  //
349  if (g_IsSerialConnectedToRemoteDebuggee)
350  {
351  KdSendEditMemoryPacketToDebuggee((DEBUGGER_EDIT_MEMORY *)FinalBuffer, FinalSize);
352  return;
353  }
354 
355  //
356  // It's on VMI mode
357  //
358  AssertShowMessageReturnStmt(g_DeviceHandle, ASSERT_MESSAGE_DRIVER_NOT_LOADED, AssertReturn);
359 
360  Status = DeviceIoControl(
361  g_DeviceHandle, // Handle to device
362  IOCTL_DEBUGGER_EDIT_MEMORY, // IO Control code
363  FinalBuffer, // Input Buffer to driver.
364  FinalSize, // Input buffer length
365  &EditMemoryRequest, // Output Buffer from driver.
366  SIZEOF_DEBUGGER_EDIT_MEMORY, // Length of output buffer in bytes.
367  NULL, // Bytes placed in buffer.
368  NULL // synchronous call
369  );
370 
371  if (!Status)
372  {
373  free(FinalBuffer);
374  ShowMessages("ioctl failed with code 0x%x\n", GetLastError());
375  return;
376  }
377 
378  if (EditMemoryRequest.Result == DEBUGGER_OPERATION_WAS_SUCCESSFULL)
379  {
380  //
381  // Was successful, nothing to do
382  //
383  }
384  else if (
385  EditMemoryRequest.Result ==
386  DEBUGGER_ERROR_EDIT_MEMORY_STATUS_INVALID_ADDRESS_BASED_ON_CURRENT_PROCESS)
387  {
388  ShowMessages("err, the address is invalid in system process layout\n");
389  }
390  else if (
391  EditMemoryRequest.Result ==
392  DEBUGGER_ERROR_EDIT_MEMORY_STATUS_INVALID_ADDRESS_BASED_ON_OTHER_PROCESS)
393  {
394  ShowMessages("err, the address is invalid based on your specific process id\n");
395  }
396  else if (EditMemoryRequest.Result ==
397  DEBUGGER_ERROR_EDIT_MEMORY_STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER)
398  {
399  ShowMessages("invalid parameter\n");
400  }
401  else
402  {
403  ShowErrorMessage(EditMemoryRequest.Result);
404  }
405 
406  //
407  // Free the malloc buffer
408  //
409  free(FinalBuffer);
410 }

75  }
76

79  //
80  if (SplittedCommand.size() == 1)

83  {
84  TrueIfProcessIdAndFalseIfProcessName = TRUE;

86  }
87  else

89  //

91  //

94  return;
95  }
96  }
97  else if (!SplittedCommand.at(1).compare("pid"))
98  {
99  TrueIfProcessIdAndFalseIfProcessName = TRUE;
100 
101  //
102  // Check for the user to not add extra arguments
103  //
104  if (SplittedCommand.size() != 3)
105  {
106  ShowMessages("incorrect use of '!hide'\n\n");
107  CommandHideHelp();
108  return;
109  }
110 
111  //
112  // It's just a pid for the process
113  //
114  if (!ConvertStringToUInt64(SplittedCommand.at(2), &TargetPid))
115  {
116  ShowMessages("incorrect process id\n\n");
117  return;
118  }
119  }
120  else if (!SplittedCommand.at(1).compare("name"))
121  {
122  TrueIfProcessIdAndFalseIfProcessName = FALSE;
123

125  // Trim the command
126  //
127  Trim(Command);
128 
129  //
130  // Remove !hide from it
131  //
132  Command.erase(0, 5);
133 
134  //
135  // remove name + space
136  //
137  Command.erase(0, 4 + 1);
138 
139  //
140  // Trim it again
141  //
142  Trim(Command);
143  }
144  else
145  {
146  //
147  // Invalid argument for the second parameter to the command
148  //
149  ShowMessages("incorrect use of '!hide'\n\n");
150  CommandHideHelp();
151  return;
152  }
153 
154  //
155  // Check if the user used !measure or not
156  //
157  if (!g_TransparentResultsMeasured || !g_CpuidAverage ||
158  !g_CpuidStandardDeviation || !g_CpuidMedian)
159  {
160  ShowMessages("the average, median and standard deviation is not measured. "
161  "Did you use '!measure' command?\n");
162  return;
163  }
164 
165  //
166  // Check if debugger is loaded or not
167  //
168  AssertShowMessageReturnStmt(g_DeviceHandle, ASSERT_MESSAGE_DRIVER_NOT_LOADED, AssertReturn);
169 
170  //
171  // We wanna hide the debugger and make transparent vm-exits
172  //
173  HideRequest.IsHide = TRUE;
174 
175  //
176  // Set the measured times cpuid
177  //
178  HideRequest.CpuidAverage = g_CpuidAverage;
179  HideRequest.CpuidMedian = g_CpuidMedian;
180  HideRequest.CpuidStandardDeviation = g_CpuidStandardDeviation;
181 
182  //
183  // Set the measured times rdtsc/p
184  //
185  HideRequest.RdtscAverage = g_RdtscAverage;
186  HideRequest.RdtscMedian = g_RdtscMedian;
187  HideRequest.RdtscStandardDeviation = g_RdtscStandardDeviation;
188 
189  HideRequest.TrueIfProcessIdAndFalseIfProcessName =
190  TrueIfProcessIdAndFalseIfProcessName;
191 
192  if (TrueIfProcessIdAndFalseIfProcessName)
193  {
194  //
195  // It's a process id
196  //
197  HideRequest.ProcId = TargetPid;
198 
199  RequestBufferSize = sizeof(DEBUGGER_HIDE_AND_TRANSPARENT_DEBUGGER_MODE);
200  }
201  else
202  {
203  //
204  // It's a process name
205  //
206  HideRequest.LengthOfProcessName = Command.size() + 1;
207  RequestBufferSize = sizeof(DEBUGGER_HIDE_AND_TRANSPARENT_DEBUGGER_MODE) +
208  Command.size() + 1;
209  }
210 
211  //
212  // Allocate the requested buffer
213  //
214  FinalRequestBuffer =
215  (PDEBUGGER_HIDE_AND_TRANSPARENT_DEBUGGER_MODE)malloc(RequestBufferSize);
216 
217  //
218  // Zero the memory
219  //
220  RtlZeroMemory(FinalRequestBuffer, RequestBufferSize);
221 
222  //
223  // Copy the buffer on the top of the final buffer
224  // to send the kernel
225  //
226  memcpy(FinalRequestBuffer, &HideRequest, sizeof(DEBUGGER_HIDE_AND_TRANSPARENT_DEBUGGER_MODE));
227 
228  //
229  // If it's a name then we should add it to the end of the buffer
230  //
231  memcpy(((UINT64 *)((UINT64)FinalRequestBuffer +
232  sizeof(DEBUGGER_HIDE_AND_TRANSPARENT_DEBUGGER_MODE))),
233  Command.c_str(),
234  Command.size());
235 
236  //
237  // Send the request to the kernel
238  //
239 
240  Status = DeviceIoControl(
241  g_DeviceHandle, // Handle to device
242  IOCTL_DEBUGGER_HIDE_AND_UNHIDE_TO_TRANSPARENT_THE_DEBUGGER, // IO Control
243  // code
244  FinalRequestBuffer, // Input Buffer to driver.
245  RequestBufferSize, // Input buffer length
246  FinalRequestBuffer, // Output Buffer from driver.
247  SIZEOF_DEBUGGER_HIDE_AND_TRANSPARENT_DEBUGGER_MODE, // Length of output
248  // buffer in bytes.
249  &ReturnedLength, // Bytes placed in buffer.
250  NULL // synchronous call
251  );
252 
253  if (!Status)
254  {
255  ShowMessages("ioctl failed with code 0x%x\n", GetLastError());
256  free(FinalRequestBuffer);
257  return;
258  }
259 
260  if (FinalRequestBuffer->KernelStatus == DEBUGGER_OPERATION_WAS_SUCCESSFULL)
261  {
262  ShowMessages("transparent debugging successfully enabled :)\n");
263  }
264  else if (FinalRequestBuffer->KernelStatus ==
265  DEBUGGER_ERROR_UNABLE_TO_HIDE_OR_UNHIDE_DEBUGGER)
266  {
267  ShowMessages("unable to hide the debugger (transparent-debugging) :(\n");
268  free(FinalRequestBuffer);
269  return;
270  }
271  else
272  {
273  ShowMessages("unknown error occurred :(\n");
274  free(FinalRequestBuffer);
275  return;
276  }
277 
278  //
279  // free the buffer
280  //
281  free(FinalRequestBuffer);
282 }

46 {
47  PDEBUGGER_GENERAL_EVENT_DETAIL Event = NULL;
48  PDEBUGGER_GENERAL_ACTION ActionBreakToDebugger = NULL;
49  PDEBUGGER_GENERAL_ACTION ActionCustomCode = NULL;
50  PDEBUGGER_GENERAL_ACTION ActionScript = NULL;
51  UINT32 EventLength;
52  UINT32 ActionBreakToDebuggerLength = 0;
53  UINT32 ActionCustomCodeLength = 0;
54  UINT32 ActionScriptLength = 0;
55  UINT64 SpecialTarget = 0;
56  BOOLEAN GetEntry = FALSE;
57  vector<string> SplittedCommandCaseSensitive {Split(Command, ' ')};
58  DEBUGGER_EVENT_PARSING_ERROR_CAUSE EventParsingErrorCause;
59 
60  //
61  // Interpret and fill the general event and action fields
62  //
63  //
64  if (!InterpretGeneralEventAndActionsFields(
65  &SplittedCommand,
66  &SplittedCommandCaseSensitive,
67  EXTERNAL_INTERRUPT_OCCURRED,
68  &Event,
69  &EventLength,
70  &ActionBreakToDebugger,
71  &ActionBreakToDebuggerLength,
72  &ActionCustomCode,
73  &ActionCustomCodeLength,
74  &ActionScript,
75  &ActionScriptLength,
76  &EventParsingErrorCause))
77  {
78  return;
79  }
80 
81  //
82  // Interpret command specific details (if any)
83  //
84  //
85  for (auto Section : SplittedCommand)
86  {
87  if (!Section.compare("!interrupt"))
88  {
89  continue;
90  }
91  else if (!GetEntry)
92  {
93  //
94  // It's probably an index
95  //
96  if (!ConvertStringToUInt64(Section, &SpecialTarget))
97  {
98  //
99  // Unkonwn parameter
100  //
101  ShowMessages("unknown parameter '%s'\n\n", Section.c_str());
102  CommandInterruptHelp();
103 
104  FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
105  return;
106  }
107  else
108  {
109  //
110  // Check if entry is valid or not
111  //
112  if (!(SpecialTarget >= 32 && SpecialTarget <= 0xff))
113  {
114  //
115  // Entry is invalid (this command is designed for just entries
116  // between 32 to 255)
117  //
118  ShowMessages("the entry should be between 0x20 to 0xFF or the "
119  "entries between 32 to 255\n\n");
120  CommandInterruptHelp();
121 
122  FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
123  return;
124  }
125  GetEntry = TRUE;
126  }
127  }
128  else
129  {
130  //
131  // Unkonwn parameter
132  //
133  ShowMessages("unknown parameter '%s'\n\n", Section.c_str());
134  CommandInterruptHelp();
135 
136  FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
137  return;
138  }
139  }
140 
141  if (SpecialTarget == 0)
142  {
143  //
144  // The user didn't set the target interrupt, even though it's possible to
145  // get all interrupts but it makes the system not resposive so it's wrong
146  // to trigger event on all interrupts and we're not going to support it
147  //
148  ShowMessages("please specify an interrupt index to monitor, HyperDbg "
149  "doesn't support to trigger events on all interrupts because "
150  "it's not reasonable and make the system unresponsive\n");
151  CommandInterruptHelp();
152 
153  FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
154  return;
155  }
156 
157  //
158  // Set the target interrupt
159  //
160  Event->OptionalParam1 = SpecialTarget;
161 
162  //
163  // Send the ioctl to the kernel for event registration
164  //
165  if (!SendEventToKernel(Event, EventLength))
166  {
167  //
168  // There was an error, probably the handle was not initialized
169  // we have to free the Action before exit, it is because, we
170  // already freed the Event and string buffers
171  //
172 
173  FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
174  return;
175  }
176 
177  //
178  // Add the event to the kernel
179  //
180  if (!RegisterActionToEvent(Event,
181  ActionBreakToDebugger,
182  ActionBreakToDebuggerLength,
183  ActionCustomCode,
184  ActionCustomCodeLength,
185  ActionScript,
186  ActionScriptLength))
187  {
188  //
189  // There was an error
190  //
191 
192  FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
193  return;
194  }
195 }

341 {
342  BOOLEAN SetPid = FALSE;
343  BOOLEAN SetSearchFilter = FALSE;
344  BOOLEAN SearchStringEntered = FALSE;
345  BOOLEAN OnlyShowKernelModules = FALSE;
346  BOOLEAN OnlyShowUserModules = FALSE;

348  char Search[MAX_PATH] = {0};
349  char * SearchString = NULL;
350 
351  //
352  // Interpret command specific details (if any)
353  //
354  for (auto Section : SplittedCommand)
355  {
356  if (!Section.compare("lm"))
357  {
358  continue;
359  }
360  else if (!Section.compare("pid") && !SetPid)
361  {
362  SetPid = TRUE;
363  }
364  else if (!Section.compare("m") && !SetSearchFilter)
365  {
366  SetSearchFilter = TRUE;
367  }
368  else if (SetPid)
369  {
370  if (!ConvertStringToUInt32(Section, &TargetPid))
371  {
372  //
373  // couldn't resolve or unkonwn parameter

380  SetPid = FALSE;
381  }
382  else if (SetSearchFilter)
383  {
384  if (Section.length() >= MAX_PATH)
385  {
386  ShowMessages("err, string is too large for search, please enter "
387  "smaller string\n");
388 
389  return;
390  }
391 
392  SearchStringEntered = TRUE;
393  strcpy(Search, Section.c_str());
394 
395  SetSearchFilter = FALSE;
396  }
397  else if (!Section.compare("km"))
398  {
399  if (OnlyShowUserModules)
400  {
401  ShowMessages("err, you cannot use both 'um', and 'km', by default "
402  "HyperDbg shows both user-mode and kernel-mode modules\n");
403  return;
404  }
405 
406  OnlyShowKernelModules = TRUE;
407  }
408  else if (!Section.compare("um"))
409  {
410  if (OnlyShowKernelModules)
411  {
412  ShowMessages("err, you cannot use both 'um', and 'km', by default "
413  "HyperDbg shows both user-mode and kernel-mode modules\n");
414  return;
415  }
416 
417  OnlyShowUserModules = TRUE;
418  }
419  else
420  {
421  //
422  // Unknown parameter
423  //
424  ShowMessages("err, couldn't resolve error at '%s'\n\n",
425  Section.c_str());
426  CommandLmHelp();
427  return;
428  }

◆ CommandMonitor()

VOID CommandMonitor ( vector< string >  SplittedCommand,
string  Command 
)

!monitor command handler

Parameters

VOID
46 {
47  PDEBUGGER_GENERAL_EVENT_DETAIL Event = NULL;
48  PDEBUGGER_GENERAL_ACTION ActionBreakToDebugger = NULL;
49  PDEBUGGER_GENERAL_ACTION ActionCustomCode = NULL;
50  PDEBUGGER_GENERAL_ACTION ActionScript = NULL;
51  UINT32 EventLength;
52  UINT32 ActionBreakToDebuggerLength = 0;
53  UINT32 ActionCustomCodeLength = 0;
54  UINT32 ActionScriptLength = 0;
55  UINT64 TargetAddress;
56  UINT64 OptionalParam1 = 0; // Set the 'from' target address
57  UINT64 OptionalParam2 = 0; // Set the 'to' target address
58  BOOLEAN SetFrom = FALSE;
59  BOOLEAN SetTo = FALSE;
60  BOOLEAN SetMode = FALSE;
61  vector<string> SplittedCommandCaseSensitive {Split(Command, ' ')};
62  UINT32 IndexInCommandCaseSensitive = 0;
63  DEBUGGER_EVENT_PARSING_ERROR_CAUSE EventParsingErrorCause;
64 
65  if (SplittedCommand.size() < 4)
66  {
67  ShowMessages("incorrect use of '!monitor'\n");
68  CommandMonitorHelp();
69  return;
70  }
71 
72  //
73  // Interpret and fill the general event and action fields
74  //
75  // We use HIDDEN_HOOK_READ_AND_WRITE here but it might be changed to
76  // HIDDEN_HOOK_READ or HIDDEN_HOOK_WRITE it is because we are not sure what
77  // kind event the user need
78  //
79  if (!InterpretGeneralEventAndActionsFields(
80  &SplittedCommand,
81  &SplittedCommandCaseSensitive,
82  HIDDEN_HOOK_READ_AND_WRITE,
83  &Event,
84  &EventLength,
85  &ActionBreakToDebugger,
86  &ActionBreakToDebuggerLength,
87  &ActionCustomCode,
88  &ActionCustomCodeLength,
89  &ActionScript,
90  &ActionScriptLength,
91  &EventParsingErrorCause))
92  {
93  return;
94  }
95 
96  //
97  // Interpret command specific details (if any)
98  //
99  for (auto Section : SplittedCommand)
100  {
101  IndexInCommandCaseSensitive++;
102 
103  if (!Section.compare("!monitor"))
104  {
105  continue;
106  }
107  else if (!Section.compare("r") && !SetMode)
108  {
109  Event->EventType = HIDDEN_HOOK_READ;
110  SetMode = TRUE;
111  }
112  else if (!Section.compare("w") && !SetMode)
113  {
114  Event->EventType = HIDDEN_HOOK_WRITE;
115  SetMode = TRUE;
116  }
117  else if ((!Section.compare("rw") || !Section.compare("wr")) && !SetMode)
118  {
119  Event->EventType = HIDDEN_HOOK_READ_AND_WRITE;
120  SetMode = TRUE;
121  }
122  else
123  {
124  //
125  // It's probably address
126  //
127  if (!SetFrom)
128  {
129  if (!SymbolConvertNameOrExprToAddress(
130  SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(IndexInCommandCaseSensitive - 1),
131  &OptionalParam1))
132  {
133  //
134  // couldn't resolve or unkonwn parameter
135  //
136  ShowMessages("err, couldn't resolve error at '%s'\n\n",
137  SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(IndexInCommandCaseSensitive - 1).c_str());
138  CommandMonitorHelp();
139 
140  FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
141  return;
142  }
143  SetFrom = TRUE;
144  }
145  else if (!SetTo)
146  {
147  if (!SymbolConvertNameOrExprToAddress(
148  SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(IndexInCommandCaseSensitive - 1),
149  &OptionalParam2))
150  {
151  //
152  // Couldn't resolve or unkonwn parameter
153  //
154  ShowMessages("err, couldn't resolve error at '%s'\n\n",
155  SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(IndexInCommandCaseSensitive - 1).c_str());
156 
157  CommandMonitorHelp();
158 
159  FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
160  return;
161  }
162  SetTo = TRUE;
163  }
164  else
165  {
166  //
167  // Unkonwn parameter
168  //
169  ShowMessages("unknown parameter '%s'\n\n", Section.c_str());
170  CommandMonitorHelp();
171 
172  FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
173  return;
174  }
175  }
176  }
177 
178  //
179  // Check for invalid order of address
180  //
181  if (OptionalParam1 > OptionalParam2)
182  {
183  //
184  // 'from' is greater than 'to'
185  //
186  ShowMessages("please choose the 'from' value first, then choose the 'to' "
187  "value\n");
188 
189  FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
190  return;
191  }
192 
193  //
194  // Check if user set the mode of !monitor or not
195  //
196  if (!SetMode)
197  {
198  ShowMessages("please specify the attribute(s) that you want to monitor (r, w, rw)\n");
199 
200  FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
201  return;
202  }
203 
204  //
205  // Set the optional parameters
206  //
207  Event->OptionalParam1 = OptionalParam1;
208  Event->OptionalParam2 = OptionalParam2;
209 
210  //
211  // Send the ioctl to the kernel for event registration
212  //
213  if (!SendEventToKernel(Event, EventLength))
214  {
215  //
216  // There was an error, probably the handle was not initialized
217  // we have to free the Action before exit, it is because, we
218  // already freed the Event and string buffers
219  //
220 
221  FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
222  return;
223  }
224 
225  //
226  // Add the event to the kernel
227  //
228  if (!RegisterActionToEvent(Event,
229  ActionBreakToDebugger,
230  ActionBreakToDebuggerLength,
231  ActionCustomCode,
232  ActionCustomCodeLength,
233  ActionScript,
234  ActionScriptLength))
235  {
236  //
237  // There was an error
238  //
239 
240  FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
241  return;
242  }
243 }

60  //
61  //
62  if (!InterpretGeneralEventAndActionsFields(
63  &SplittedCommand,
64  &SplittedCommandCaseSensitive,
65  WRMSR_INSTRUCTION_EXECUTION,
66  &Event,
67  &EventLength,
68  &ActionBreakToDebugger,
69  &ActionBreakToDebuggerLength,
70  &ActionCustomCode,
71  &ActionCustomCodeLength,
72  &ActionScript,
73  &ActionScriptLength,
74  &EventParsingErrorCause))
75  {
76  return;
77  }
78 
79  //
80  // Interpret command specific details (if any), it is because we can use
81  // special msr bitmap here
82  //
83  for (auto Section : SplittedCommand)
84  {
85  if (!Section.compare("!msrwrite"))
86  {
87  continue;
88  }
89  else if (!GetAddress)
90  {
91  //
92  // It's probably an msr
93  //
94  if (!ConvertStringToUInt64(Section, &SpecialTarget))
95  {
96  //
97  // Unkonwn parameter
98  //
99  ShowMessages("unknown parameter '%s'\n\n", Section.c_str());
100  CommandMsrwriteHelp();
101 
102  FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
103  return;
104  }
105  else
106  {
107  GetAddress = TRUE;
108  }
109  }
110  else
111  {
112  //
113  // Unkonwn parameter
114  //
115  ShowMessages("unknown parameter '%s'\n\n", Section.c_str());
116  CommandMsrwriteHelp();
117 
118  FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
119  return;
120  }
121  }
122 
123  //
124  // Set the target msr (if not specific then it means all msrs)
125  //
126  Event->OptionalParam1 = SpecialTarget;
127 
128  //
129  // Send the ioctl to the kernel for event registration
130  //
131  if (!SendEventToKernel(Event, EventLength))
132  {
133  //
134  // There was an error, probably the handle was not initialized
135  // we have to free the Action before exit, it is because, we
136  // already freed the Event and string buffers
137  //
138 
139  FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
140  return;
141  }
142 
143  //
144  // Add the event to the kernel
145  //
146  if (!RegisterActionToEvent(Event,
147  ActionBreakToDebugger,
148  ActionBreakToDebuggerLength,
149  ActionCustomCode,
150  ActionCustomCodeLength,
151  ActionScript,
152  ActionScriptLength))
153  {
154  //
155  // There was an error
156  //
157 
158  FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
159  return;
160  }
161 }

85  SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(1).c_str());
86  return;
87  }
88  }
89  else
90  {
91  //
92  // It might be address + pid
93  //
94  if (!SplittedCommand.at(1).compare("pid"))
95  {
96  if (!ConvertStringToUInt32(SplittedCommand.at(2), &Pid))
97  {
98  ShowMessages("incorrect address, please enter a valid process id\n");
99  return;
100  }
101  if (!SymbolConvertNameOrExprToAddress(SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(3), &TargetPa))
102  {
103  //
104  // Couldn't resolve or unkonwn parameter
105  //
106  ShowMessages("err, couldn't resolve error at '%s'\n",
107  SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(3).c_str());
108  return;
109  }
110  }
111  else if (!SplittedCommand.at(2).compare("pid"))
112  {
113  if (!SymbolConvertNameOrExprToAddress(SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(1), &TargetPa))
114  {
115  //
116  // Couldn't resolve or unkonwn parameter
117  //
118  ShowMessages("err, couldn't resolve error at '%s'\n",
119  SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(1).c_str());
120 
121  return;
122  }
123  if (!ConvertStringToUInt32(SplittedCommand.at(3), &Pid))
124  {
125  ShowMessages("incorrect address, please enter a valid process id\n");
126  return;
127  }
128  }
129  else
130  {
131  ShowMessages("incorrect use of '!pa2va'\n\n");
132  CommandPa2vaHelp();
133  return;
134  }
135  }
136 
137  //
138  // Prepare the buffer
139  // We use same buffer for input and output
140  //
141  AddressDetails.PhysicalAddress = TargetPa;
142  AddressDetails.ProcessId = Pid; // it's null if in debugger mode
143  AddressDetails.IsVirtual2Physical = FALSE;
144 
145  if (g_IsSerialConnectedToRemoteDebuggee)
146  {
147  //
148  // Check to prevent using process id in !pa2va command
149  //
150  if (Pid != 0)
151  {
152  ShowMessages("err, you cannot specify 'pid' in the debugger mode\n");
153  return;
154  }
155 
156  //
157  // Send the request over serial kernel debugger
158  //
159 
160  KdSendVa2paAndPa2vaPacketToDebuggee(&AddressDetails);
161  }
162  else
163  {
164  AssertShowMessageReturnStmt(g_DeviceHandle, ASSERT_MESSAGE_DRIVER_NOT_LOADED, AssertReturn);
165 
166  if (Pid == 0)
167  {
168  Pid = GetCurrentProcessId();
169  AddressDetails.ProcessId = Pid;
170  }
171 
172  //
173  // Send IOCTL
174  //
175  Status = DeviceIoControl(
176  g_DeviceHandle, // Handle to device
177  IOCTL_DEBUGGER_VA2PA_AND_PA2VA_COMMANDS, // IO Control code
178  &AddressDetails, // Input Buffer to driver.
179  SIZEOF_DEBUGGER_VA2PA_AND_PA2VA_COMMANDS, // Input buffer length
180  &AddressDetails, // Output Buffer from driver.
181  SIZEOF_DEBUGGER_VA2PA_AND_PA2VA_COMMANDS, // Length of output
182  // buffer in bytes.
183  &ReturnedLength, // Bytes placed in buffer.
184  NULL // synchronous call
185  );
186 
187  if (!Status)
188  {
189  ShowMessages("ioctl failed with code 0x%x\n", GetLastError());
190  return;
191  }
192 
193  if (AddressDetails.KernelStatus == DEBUGGER_OPERATION_WAS_SUCCESSFULL)
194  {
195  //
196  // Show the results
197  //
198  ShowMessages("%llx\n", AddressDetails.VirtualAddress);
199  }
200  else
201  {
202  //
203  // An err occurred, no results
204  //
205  ShowErrorMessage(AddressDetails.KernelStatus);
206  }
207  }
208 }

150  }

158  }
159  }
160  else

162  ShowMessages(
163  "err, unknown parameter at '%s'\n\n",
164  SplittedCommand.at(1).c_str());
165  CommandProcessHelp();
166  return;
167  }
168  }

170  {
171  //
172  // Check if it's connected to a remote debuggee or not
173  //

175  {
176  ShowMessages("err, you're not connected to any debuggee in Debugger Mode, "
177  "you can use the '.attach', or the '.detach' commands if you're "

179  return;

233  return;
234  }
235

237  {

51  if (SplittedCommand.size() >= 5)
52  {

55  return;
56  }
57

59  {

61  {
62  continue;
63  }
64

66  {
67  if (!ConvertStringToUInt32(Section, &CoreNumer))
68  {
69  ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex value for core id\n\n");
70  CommandRdmsrHelp();
71  return;
72  }
73  IsNextCoreId = FALSE;
74  continue;

78  {
79  IsNextCoreId = TRUE;
80  continue;
81  }

84  {
85  ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex value to be read\n\n");
86  CommandRdmsrHelp();
87  return;
88  }
89  SetMsr = TRUE;
90  }
91 
92  //
93  // Check if msr is set or not
94  //
95  if (!SetMsr)
96  {
97  ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex value to be read\n\n");
98  CommandRdmsrHelp();
99  return;
100  }

102  {
103  ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex value for core\n\n");
104  CommandRdmsrHelp();
105  return;
106  }
107 
108  AssertShowMessageReturnStmt(g_DeviceHandle, ASSERT_MESSAGE_DRIVER_NOT_LOADED, AssertReturn);
109

111  MsrReadRequest.Msr = Msr;
112  MsrReadRequest.CoreNumber = CoreNumer;
113 
114  //
115  // Find logical cores count
116  //
117  GetSystemInfo(&SysInfo);
118  NumCPU = SysInfo.dwNumberOfProcessors;
119 
120  //
121  // allocate buffer for transfering messages
122  //
123  UINT64 * OutputBuffer = (UINT64 *)malloc(sizeof(UINT64) * NumCPU);
124 
125  ZeroMemory(OutputBuffer, sizeof(UINT64) * NumCPU);
126 
127  Status = DeviceIoControl(
128  g_DeviceHandle, // Handle to device
129  IOCTL_DEBUGGER_READ_OR_WRITE_MSR, // IO Control code
130  &MsrReadRequest, // Input Buffer to driver.

132  OutputBuffer, // Output Buffer from driver.
133  sizeof(UINT64) * NumCPU, // Length of output buffer in bytes.
134  &ReturnedLength, // Bytes placed in buffer.
135  NULL // synchronous call
136  );
137 
138  if (!Status)
139  {

141  GetLastError());
142  free(OutputBuffer);
143  return;
144  }
145 
146  //
147  // btw, %x is enough, no need to %llx
148  //

150  {
151  //
152  // Show all cores
153  //
154  for (size_t i = 0; i < NumCPU; i++)
155  {
156  ShowMessages("core : 0x%x - msr[%llx] = %s\n", i, Msr, SeparateTo64BitValue((OutputBuffer[i])).c_str());
157  }
158  }
159  else

161  //
162  // Show for a single-core
163  //
164  ShowMessages("core : 0x%x - msr[%llx] = %s\n", CoreNumer, Msr, SeparateTo64BitValue((OutputBuffer[0])).c_str());
165  }
166

168  // Free the buffer
169  //

◆ CommandSearchMemory()

VOID CommandSearchMemory ( vector< string >  SplittedCommand,
string  Command 
)

!s* s* commands handler

Parameters
SplittedCommand
Command
Returns
VOID
139 {
140  BOOL SetAddress = FALSE;
141  BOOL SetValue = FALSE;
142  BOOL SetProcId = FALSE;
143  BOOL NextIsProcId = FALSE;
144  BOOL SetLength = FALSE;
145  BOOL NextIsLength = FALSE;
146  DEBUGGER_SEARCH_MEMORY SearchMemoryRequest = {0};
147  UINT64 Address;
148  UINT64 Value = 0;
149  UINT64 Length = 0;
150  UINT32 ProcId = 0;
151  UINT32 CountOfValues = 0;
152  UINT32 FinalSize = 0;
153  UINT64 * FinalBuffer = NULL;
154  vector<UINT64> ValuesToEdit;
155  vector<string> SplittedCommandCaseSensitive {Split(Command, ' ')};
156  UINT32 IndexInCommandCaseSensitive = 0;
157 
158  //
159  // By default if the user-debugger is active, we use these commands
160  // on the memory layout of the debuggee process
161  //
162  if (g_ActiveProcessDebuggingState.IsActive)
163  {
164  ProcId = g_ActiveProcessDebuggingState.ProcessId;
165  }
166 
167  if (SplittedCommand.size() <= 4)
168  {
169  ShowMessages("incorrect use of 's*'\n\n");
170  CommandSearchMemoryHelp();
171  return;
172  }
173 
174  for (auto Section : SplittedCommand)
175  {
176  IndexInCommandCaseSensitive++;
177 
178  if (!Section.compare(SplittedCommand.at(0)))
179  {
180  if (!Section.compare("!sb"))
181  {
182  SearchMemoryRequest.MemoryType = SEARCH_PHYSICAL_MEMORY;
183  SearchMemoryRequest.ByteSize = SEARCH_BYTE;
184  }
185  else if (!Section.compare("!sd"))
186  {
187  SearchMemoryRequest.MemoryType = SEARCH_PHYSICAL_MEMORY;
188  SearchMemoryRequest.ByteSize = SEARCH_DWORD;
189  }
190  else if (!Section.compare("!sq"))
191  {
192  SearchMemoryRequest.MemoryType = SEARCH_PHYSICAL_MEMORY;
193  SearchMemoryRequest.ByteSize = SEARCH_QWORD;
194  }
195  else if (!Section.compare("sb"))
196  {
197  SearchMemoryRequest.MemoryType = SEARCH_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
198  SearchMemoryRequest.ByteSize = SEARCH_BYTE;
199  }
200  else if (!Section.compare("sd"))
201  {
202  SearchMemoryRequest.MemoryType = SEARCH_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
203  SearchMemoryRequest.ByteSize = SEARCH_DWORD;
204  }
205  else if (!Section.compare("sq"))
206  {
207  SearchMemoryRequest.MemoryType = SEARCH_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
208  SearchMemoryRequest.ByteSize = SEARCH_QWORD;
209  }
210  else
211  {
212  //
213  // What's this? :(
214  //
215  ShowMessages("unknown error happened !\n\n");
216  CommandSearchMemoryHelp();
217  return;
218  }
219 
220  continue;
221  }
222 
223  if (NextIsProcId)
224  {
225  //
226  // It's a process id
227  //
228  NextIsProcId = FALSE;
229 
230  if (!ConvertStringToUInt32(Section, &ProcId))
231  {
232  ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex prcoess id\n\n");
233  CommandSearchMemoryHelp();
234  return;
235  }
236  else
237  {
238  //
239  // Means that the proc id is set, next we should read value
240  //
241  continue;
242  }
243  }
244 
245  if (NextIsLength)
246  {
247  //
248  // It's a length
249  //
250  NextIsLength = FALSE;
251 
252  if (!ConvertStringToUInt64(Section, &Length))
253  {
254  ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex length\n\n");
255  CommandSearchMemoryHelp();
256  return;
257  }
258  else
259  {
260  //
261  // Means that the proc id is set, next we should read value
262  //
263  SetLength = TRUE;
264  continue;
265  }
266  }
267 
268  //
269  // Check if it's a process id or not
270  //
271  if (!SetProcId && !Section.compare("pid"))
272  {
273  NextIsProcId = TRUE;
274  continue;
275  }
276 
277  //
278  // Check if it's a length or not
279  //
280  if (!SetLength && !Section.compare("l"))
281  {
282  NextIsLength = TRUE;
283  continue;
284  }
285 
286  if (!SetAddress)
287  {
288  if (!SymbolConvertNameOrExprToAddress(SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(IndexInCommandCaseSensitive - 1), &Address))
289  {
290  ShowMessages("err, couldn't resolve error at '%s'\n\n",
291  SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(IndexInCommandCaseSensitive - 1).c_str());
292  CommandSearchMemoryHelp();
293  return;
294  }
295  else
296  {
297  //
298  // Means that the address is set, next we should read value
299  //
300  SetAddress = TRUE;
301  continue;
302  }
303  }
304 
305  if (SetAddress)
306  {
307  //
308  // Remove the hex notations
309  //
310  if (Section.rfind("0x", 0) == 0 || Section.rfind("0X", 0) == 0 ||
311  Section.rfind("\\x", 0) == 0 || Section.rfind("\\X", 0) == 0)
312  {
313  Section = Section.erase(0, 2);
314  }
315  else if (Section.rfind('x', 0) == 0 || Section.rfind('X', 0) == 0)
316  {
317  Section = Section.erase(0, 1);
318  }
319  Section.erase(remove(Section.begin(), Section.end(), '`'), Section.end());
320 
321  //
322  // Check if the value is valid based on byte counts
323  //
324  if (SearchMemoryRequest.ByteSize == SEARCH_BYTE && Section.size() >= 3)
325  {
326  ShowMessages("please specify a byte (hex) value for 'sb' or '!sb'\n\n");
327  return;
328  }
329  if (SearchMemoryRequest.ByteSize == SEARCH_DWORD && Section.size() >= 9)
330  {
331  ShowMessages(
332  "please specify a dword (hex) value for 'sd' or '!sd'\n\n");
333  return;
334  }
335  if (SearchMemoryRequest.ByteSize == SEARCH_QWORD &&
336  Section.size() >= 17)
337  {
338  ShowMessages(
339  "please specify a qword (hex) value for 'sq' or '!sq'\n\n");
340  return;
341  }
342 
343  //
344  // Qword is checked by the following function, no need to double
345  // check it above.
346  //
347  if (!ConvertStringToUInt64(Section, &Value))
348  {
349  ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex value to search in the "
350  "memory content\n\n");
351  CommandSearchMemoryHelp();
352  return;
353  }
354  else
355  {
356  //
357  // Add it to the list
358  //
359  ValuesToEdit.push_back(Value);
360 
361  //
362  // Keep track of values to modify
363  //
364  CountOfValues++;
365 
366  if (!SetValue)
367  {
368  //
369  // At least on walue is there
370  //
371  SetValue = TRUE;
372  }
373  continue;
374  }
375  }
376  }
377 
378  //
379  // Check to prevent using process id in s* commands
380  //
381  if (g_IsSerialConnectedToRemoteDebuggee && ProcId != 0)
382  {
383  ShowMessages("err, you cannot specify 'pid' in the debugger mode\n");
384  return;
385  }
386 
387  if (ProcId == 0)
388  {
389  ProcId = GetCurrentProcessId();
390  }
391 
392  //
393  // Fill the structure
394  //
395  SearchMemoryRequest.ProcessId = ProcId;
396  SearchMemoryRequest.Address = Address;
397  SearchMemoryRequest.CountOf64Chunks = CountOfValues;
398 
399  //
400  // Check if address and value are set or not
401  //
402  if (!SetAddress)
403  {
404  ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex address\n\n");
405  CommandSearchMemoryHelp();
406  return;
407  }
408  if (!SetValue)
409  {
410  ShowMessages(
411  "please specify a correct hex value as the content to search\n\n");
412  CommandSearchMemoryHelp();
413  return;
414  }
415  if (!SetLength)
416  {
417  ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex value as the length\n\n");
418  CommandSearchMemoryHelp();
419  return;
420  }
421  if (NextIsProcId)
422  {
423  ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex value as the process id\n\n");
424  CommandSearchMemoryHelp();
425  return;
426  }
427  if (NextIsLength)
428  {
429  ShowMessages("please specify a correct hex length\n\n");
430  CommandSearchMemoryHelp();
431  return;
432  }
433 
434  //
435  // Now it's time to put everything together in one structure
436  //
437  FinalSize = (CountOfValues * sizeof(UINT64)) + SIZEOF_DEBUGGER_SEARCH_MEMORY;
438 
439  //
440  // Set the size
441  //
442  SearchMemoryRequest.FinalStructureSize = FinalSize;
443 
444  //
445  // Set the length
446  //
447  SearchMemoryRequest.Length = Length;
448 
449  if (!g_IsSerialConnectedToRemoteDebuggee)
450  {
451  AssertShowMessageReturnStmt(g_DeviceHandle, ASSERT_MESSAGE_DRIVER_NOT_LOADED, AssertReturn);
452  }
453 
454  //
455  // Allocate structure + buffer
456  //
457  FinalBuffer = (UINT64 *)malloc(FinalSize);
458 
459  if (!FinalBuffer)
460  {
461  ShowMessages("unable to allocate memory\n\n");
462  return;
463  }
464 
465  //
466  // Zero the buffer
467  //
468  ZeroMemory(FinalBuffer, FinalSize);
469 
470  //
471  // Copy the structure on top of the allocated buffer
472  //
473  memcpy(FinalBuffer, &SearchMemoryRequest, SIZEOF_DEBUGGER_SEARCH_MEMORY);
474 
475  //
476  // Put the values in 64 bit structures
477  //
478  std::copy(ValuesToEdit.begin(), ValuesToEdit.end(), (UINT64 *)((UINT64)FinalBuffer + SIZEOF_DEBUGGER_SEARCH_MEMORY));
479 
480  //
481  // Check if it's a connection in debugger mode
482  //
483  if (g_IsSerialConnectedToRemoteDebuggee)
484  {
485  //
486  // The buffer should be sent to the debugger
487  //
488  KdSendSearchRequestPacketToDebuggee(FinalBuffer, FinalSize);
489  }
490  else
491  {
492  //
493  // it's a local connection, send the buffer directly
494  //
495  CommandSearchSendRequest(FinalBuffer, FinalSize);
496  }
497 
498  //
499  // Free the buffers
500  //
501  free(FinalBuffer);
502 }

52  //
53 #if ActivateUserModeDebugger == FALSE
54 
55  if (!g_IsSerialConnectedToRemoteDebugger)
56  {
57  ShowMessages("The user-mode debugger is still in the beta version and not stable. "
58  "We decided to exclude it from this release and release it in future versions. "
59  "If you want to test the user-mode debugger in VMI Mode, you should build "
60  "HyperDbg with special instructions. \nPlease follow the steps here: "
61  "https://docs.hyperdbg.org/getting-started/build-and-install \n");
62  return;
63  }
64 
65 #endif // !ActivateUserModeDebugger
66 
67  if (SplittedCommand.size() <= 2)
68  {
69  ShowMessages("incorrect use of '.start'\n\n");
70  CommandStartHelp();
71  return;
72  }
73 
74  if (!SplittedCommand.at(1).compare("path"))
75  {
76  //
77  // *** It's a run of target PE file ***
78  //
79 
80  //
81  // Trim the command
82  //
83  Trim(Command);
84 
85  //
86  // Remove .start from it
87  //
88  Command.erase(0, 6);
89 
90  //
91  // Remove path + space
92  //
93  Command.erase(0, 4 + 1);
94 
95  //
96  // Trim it again
97  //
98  Trim(Command);
99 
100  //
101  // Split Path and args
102  //
103  SplitPathAndArgs(PathAndArgs, Command);
104 
105  //
106  // Convert path to wstring
107  //
108  StringToWString(g_StartCommandPath, PathAndArgs.at(0));
109 
110  if (PathAndArgs.size() != 1)
111  {
112  //
113  // There are arguments to this command
114  //
115 
116  for (auto item : PathAndArgs)
117  {
118  //
119  // Append the arguments
120  //
121  // ShowMessages("Arg : %s\n", item.c_str());
122  Arguments += item + " ";
123  }
124 
125  //
126  // Remove the latest space
127  //
128  Arguments.pop_back();
129 
130  //
131  // Convert arguments to wstring
132  //
133  StringToWString(g_StartCommandPathAndArguments, Arguments);
134  }
135  }
136  else
137  {
138  ShowMessages("err, couldn't resolve error at '%s'\n\n",
139  SplittedCommand.at(1).c_str());
140  CommandStartHelp();
141  return;
142  }
143 
144  //
145  // Perform run of the target file
146  //
147  if (Arguments.empty())
148  {
149  UdAttachToProcess(NULL,
150  g_StartCommandPath.c_str(),
151  NULL);
152  }
153  else
154  {
155  UdAttachToProcess(NULL,
156  g_StartCommandPath.c_str(),
157  (WCHAR *)g_StartCommandPathAndArguments.c_str());
158  }
159 }

172 
173  if (!Cmd.compare("!syscall") || !Cmd.compare("!syscall2"))
174  {
175  CommandSyscallHelp();
176  }
177  else
178  {
179  CommandSysretHelp();
180  }
181 
182  FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
183  return;
184  }
185  else
186  {
187  GetSyscallNumber = TRUE;
188  }
189  }
190  else
191  {
192  //
193  // Unkonwn parameter
194  //
195  ShowMessages("unknown parameter '%s'\n\n", Section.c_str());
196 
197  if (!Cmd.compare("!syscall") || !Cmd.compare("!syscall2"))
198  {
199  CommandSyscallHelp();
200  }
201  else
202  {
203  CommandSysretHelp();
204  }
205 
206  FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
207  return;
208  }
209  }
210 
211  //
212  // Set the target syscall
213  //
214  Event->OptionalParam1 = SpecialTarget;
215  }
216 
217  //
218  // Set whether it's !syscall or !syscall2 or !sysret or !sysret2
219  //
220  if (!Cmd.compare("!syscall2") || !Cmd.compare("!sysret2"))
221  {
222  //
223  // It's a !syscall2 or !sysret2
224  //
225  Event->OptionalParam2 = DEBUGGER_EVENT_SYSCALL_SYSRET_HANDLE_ALL_UD;
226  }
227  else
228  {
229  //
230  // It's a !syscall or !sysret
231  //
232  Event->OptionalParam2 = DEBUGGER_EVENT_SYSCALL_SYSRET_SAFE_ACCESS_MEMORY;
233  }
234 
235  //
236  // Send the ioctl to the kernel for event registration
237  //
238  if (!SendEventToKernel(Event, EventLength))
239  {
240  //
241  // There was an error, probably the handle was not initialized
242  // we have to free the Action before exit, it is because, we
243  // already freed the Event and string buffers
244  //
245 
246  FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
247  return;
248  }
249 
250  //
251  // Add the event to the kernel
252  //
253  if (!RegisterActionToEvent(Event,
254  ActionBreakToDebugger,
255  ActionBreakToDebuggerLength,
256  ActionCustomCode,
257  ActionCustomCodeLength,
258  ActionScript,
259  ActionScriptLength))
260  {
261  //
262  // There was an error
263  //
264 
265  FreeEventsAndActionsMemory(Event, ActionBreakToDebugger, ActionCustomCode, ActionScript);
266  return;
267  }
268 }

72  Pid = g_ActiveProcessDebuggingState.ProcessId;
73  }
74 
75  if (SplittedCommand.size() == 2)
76  {
77  //
78  // It's just an address for current process
79  //
80  if (!SymbolConvertNameOrExprToAddress(SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(1), &TargetVa))
81  {
82  //
83  // Couldn't resolve or unkonwn parameter
84  //
85  ShowMessages("err, couldn't resolve error at '%s'\n",
86  SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(1).c_str());
87  return;
88  }
89  }
90  else
91  {
92  //
93  // It might be address + pid
94  //
95  if (!SplittedCommand.at(1).compare("pid"))
96  {
97  if (!ConvertStringToUInt32(SplittedCommand.at(2), &Pid))
98  {
99  ShowMessages("incorrect address, please enter a valid process id\n");
100  return;
101  }
102 
103  if (!SymbolConvertNameOrExprToAddress(SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(3), &TargetVa))
104  {
105  //
106  // Couldn't resolve or unkonwn parameter
107  //
108  ShowMessages("err, couldn't resolve error at '%s'\n",
109  SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(3).c_str());
110  return;
111  }
112  }
113  else if (!SplittedCommand.at(2).compare("pid"))
114  {
115  if (!SymbolConvertNameOrExprToAddress(SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(1), &TargetVa))
116  {
117  //
118  // Couldn't resolve or unkonwn parameter
119  //
120  ShowMessages("err, couldn't resolve error at '%s'\n",
121  SplittedCommandCaseSensitive.at(1).c_str());
122  return;
123  }
124 
125  if (!ConvertStringToUInt32(SplittedCommand.at(3), &Pid))
126  {
127  ShowMessages("incorrect address, please enter a valid process id\n");
128  return;
129  }
130  }
131  else
132  {
133  ShowMessages("incorrect use of '!va2pa'\n\n");
134  CommandVa2paHelp();
135  return;
136  }
137  }
138 
139  //
140  // Prepare the buffer
141  // We use same buffer for input and output
142  //
143  AddressDetails.VirtualAddress = TargetVa;
144  AddressDetails.ProcessId = Pid; // null in debugger mode
145  AddressDetails.IsVirtual2Physical = TRUE;
146 
147  if (g_IsSerialConnectedToRemoteDebuggee)
148  {
149  //
150  // Check to prevent using process id in !va2pa command
151  //
152  if (Pid != 0)
153  {
154  ShowMessages("err, you cannot specify 'pid' in the debugger mode\n");
155  return;
156  }
157 
158  //
159  // Send the request over serial kernel debugger
160  //
161 
162  KdSendVa2paAndPa2vaPacketToDebuggee(&AddressDetails);
163  }
164  else
165  {
166  AssertShowMessageReturnStmt(g_DeviceHandle, ASSERT_MESSAGE_DRIVER_NOT_LOADED, AssertReturn);
167 
168  if (Pid == 0)
169  {
170  Pid = GetCurrentProcessId();
171  AddressDetails.ProcessId = Pid;
172  }
173 
174  //
175  // Send IOCTL
176  //
177  Status = DeviceIoControl(
178  g_DeviceHandle, // Handle to device
179  IOCTL_DEBUGGER_VA2PA_AND_PA2VA_COMMANDS, // IO Control code
180  &AddressDetails, // Input Buffer to driver.
181  SIZEOF_DEBUGGER_VA2PA_AND_PA2VA_COMMANDS, // Input buffer length
182  &AddressDetails, // Output Buffer from driver.
183  SIZEOF_DEBUGGER_VA2PA_AND_PA2VA_COMMANDS, // Length of output
184  // buffer in bytes.
185  &ReturnedLength, // Bytes placed in buffer.
186  NULL // synchronous call
187  );
188 
189  if (!Status)
190  {
191  ShowMessages("ioctl failed with code 0x%x\n", GetLastError());
192  return;
193  }
194 
195  if (AddressDetails.KernelStatus == DEBUGGER_OPERATION_WAS_SUCCESSFULL)
196  {
197  //
198  // Show the results
199  //
200  ShowMessages("%llx\n", AddressDetails.PhysicalAddress);
201  }
202  else
203  {
204  //
205  // An err occurred, no results
206  //
207  ShowErrorMessage(AddressDetails.KernelStatus);
208  }
209  }
210 }

)

Check whether the jump is taken or not taken (in debugger)

the implementation of this function derived from the table in this site : http://www.unixwiz.net/techtips/x86-jumps.html

Parameters
BufferToDisassembleCurrent Bytes of assembly
BuffLengthLength of buffer
RflagsThe kernel's currnet RFLAG
Isx86_64Whether it's an x86 or x64
Returns
DEBUGGER_NEXT_INSTRUCTION_FINDER_STATUS
415 {
416  ZydisDecoder decoder;
417  ZydisFormatter formatter;
418  UINT64 CurrentRip = 0;
419  int instr_decoded = 0;
420  ZydisDecodedInstruction instruction;
421  char buffer[256];
422  UINT32 MaximumInstrDecoded = 1;
423 
424  if (ZydisGetVersion() != ZYDIS_VERSION)
425  {
426  ShowMessages("invalid zydis version\n");
427  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_ERROR;
428  }
429 
430  if (Isx86_64)
431  {
432  ZydisDecoderInit(&decoder, ZYDIS_MACHINE_MODE_LONG_64, ZYDIS_ADDRESS_WIDTH_64);
433  }
434  else
435  {
436  ZydisDecoderInit(&decoder, ZYDIS_MACHINE_MODE_LONG_COMPAT_32, ZYDIS_ADDRESS_WIDTH_32);
437  }
438 
439  ZydisFormatterInit(&formatter, ZYDIS_FORMATTER_STYLE_INTEL);
440 
441  ZydisFormatterSetProperty(&formatter, ZYDIS_FORMATTER_PROP_FORCE_SEGMENT, ZYAN_TRUE);
442  ZydisFormatterSetProperty(&formatter, ZYDIS_FORMATTER_PROP_FORCE_SIZE, ZYAN_TRUE);
443 
444  //
445  // Replace the `ZYDIS_FORMATTER_FUNC_PRINT_ADDRESS_ABS` function that
446  // formats the absolute addresses
447  //
448  default_print_address_absolute =
449  (ZydisFormatterFunc)&ZydisFormatterPrintAddressAbsolute;
450  ZydisFormatterSetHook(&formatter, ZYDIS_FORMATTER_FUNC_PRINT_ADDRESS_ABS, (const void **)&default_print_address_absolute);
451 
452  while (ZYAN_SUCCESS(ZydisDecoderDecodeBuffer(&decoder, BufferToDisassemble, BuffLength, &instruction)))
453  {
454  //
455  // We have to pass a `runtime_address` different to
456  // `ZYDIS_RUNTIME_ADDRESS_NONE` to enable printing of absolute addresses
457  //
458 
459  ZydisFormatterFormatInstruction(&formatter, &instruction, &buffer[0], sizeof(buffer), (ZyanU64)CurrentRip);
460 
461  switch (instruction.mnemonic)
462  {
463  case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JO:
464 
465  //
466  // Jump if overflow (jo)
467  //
468  if (Rflags.OverflowFlag)
469  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN;
470  else
471  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN;
472 
473  break;
474 
475  case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JNO:
476 
477  //
478  // Jump if not overflow (jno)
479  //
480  if (!Rflags.OverflowFlag)
481  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN;
482  else
483  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN;
484 
485  break;
486 
487  case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JS:
488 
489  //
490  // Jump if sign
491  //
492  if (Rflags.SignFlag)
493  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN;
494  else
495  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN;
496 
497  break;
498 
499  case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JNS:
500 
501  //
502  // Jump if not sign
503  //
504  if (!Rflags.SignFlag)
505  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN;
506  else
507  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN;
508 
509  break;
510 
511  case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JZ:
512 
513  //
514  // Jump if equal (je),
515  // Jump if zero (jz)
516  //
517  if (Rflags.ZeroFlag)
518  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN;
519  else
520  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN;
521 
522  break;
523 
524  case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JNZ:
525 
526  //
527  // Jump if not equal (jne),
528  // Jump if not zero (jnz)
529  //
530  if (!Rflags.ZeroFlag)
531  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN;
532  else
533  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN;
534 
535  break;
536 
537  case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JB:
538 
539  //
540  // Jump if below (jb),
541  // Jump if not above or equal (jnae),
542  // Jump if carry (jc)
543  //
544 
545  //
546  // This jump is unsigned
547  //
548 
549  if (Rflags.CarryFlag)
550  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN;
551  else
552  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN;
553 
554  break;
555 
556  case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JNB:
557 
558  //
559  // Jump if not below (jnb),
560  // Jump if above or equal (jae),
561  // Jump if not carry (jnc)
562  //
563 
564  //
565  // This jump is unsigned
566  //
567 
568  if (!Rflags.CarryFlag)
569  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN;
570  else
571  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN;
572 
573  break;
574 
575  case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JBE:
576 
577  //
578  // Jump if below or equal (jbe),
579  // Jump if not above (jna)
580  //
581 
582  //
583  // This jump is unsigned
584  //
585 
586  if (Rflags.CarryFlag || Rflags.ZeroFlag)
587  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN;
588  else
589  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN;
590 
591  break;
592 
593  case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JNBE:
594 
595  //
596  // Jump if above (ja),
597  // Jump if not below or equal (jnbe)
598  //
599 
600  //
601  // This jump is unsigned
602  //
603 
604  if (!Rflags.CarryFlag && !Rflags.ZeroFlag)
605  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN;
606  else
607  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN;
608 
609  break;
610 
611  case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JL:
612 
613  //
614  // Jump if less (jl),
615  // Jump if not greater or equal (jnge)
616  //
617 
618  //
619  // This jump is signed
620  //
621 
622  if (Rflags.SignFlag != Rflags.OverflowFlag)
623  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN;
624  else
625  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN;
626 
627  break;
628 
629  case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JNL:
630 
631  //
632  // Jump if greater or equal (jge),
633  // Jump if not less (jnl)
634  //
635 
636  //
637  // This jump is signed
638  //
639 
640  if (Rflags.SignFlag == Rflags.OverflowFlag)
641  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN;
642  else
643  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN;
644 
645  break;
646 
647  case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JLE:
648 
649  //
650  // Jump if less or equal (jle),
651  // Jump if not greater (jng)
652  //
653 
654  //
655  // This jump is signed
656  //
657 
658  if (Rflags.ZeroFlag || Rflags.SignFlag != Rflags.OverflowFlag)
659  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN;
660  else
661  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN;
662 
663  break;
664 
665  case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JNLE:
666 
667  //
668  // Jump if greater (jg),
669  // Jump if not less or equal (jnle)
670  //
671 
672  //
673  // This jump is signed
674  //
675 
676  if (!Rflags.ZeroFlag && Rflags.SignFlag == Rflags.OverflowFlag)
677  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN;
678  else
679  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN;
680 
681  break;
682 
683  case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JP:
684 
685  //
686  // Jump if parity (jp),
687  // Jump if parity even (jpe)
688  //
689 
690  if (Rflags.ParityFlag)
691  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN;
692  else
693  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN;
694 
695  break;
696 
697  case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JNP:
698 
699  //
700  // Jump if not parity (jnp),
701  // Jump if parity odd (jpo)
702  //
703 
704  if (!Rflags.ParityFlag)
705  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN;
706  else
707  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN;
708 
709  break;
710 
711  case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JCXZ:
712  case ZydisMnemonic::ZYDIS_MNEMONIC_JECXZ:
713 
714  //
715  // Jump if %CX register is 0 (jcxz),
716  // Jump if% ECX register is 0 (jecxz)
717  //
718 
719  //
720  // Actually this instruction are rarely used
721  // but if we want to suport these instructions then we
722  // should read ecx and cx each time in the debuggee,
723  // so it's better to just ignore it as a non-conditional
724  // jump
725  //
726  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_NOT_CONDITIONAL_JUMP;
727 
728  default:
729 
730  //
731  // It's not a jump
732  //
733  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_NOT_CONDITIONAL_JUMP;
734  break;
735  }
736 
737  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_ERROR;
738  }
739 }
DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN
@ DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_NOT_TAKEN
Definition: Definition.h:2319
DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN
@ DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_JUMP_IS_TAKEN
Definition: Definition.h:2318
DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_NOT_CONDITIONAL_JUMP
@ DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_NOT_CONDITIONAL_JUMP

UINT32 HyperDbgLengthDisassemblerEngine ( unsigned char *  BufferToDisassemble,
UINT64  BuffLength,
BOOLEAN  Isx86_64 
)

Length Disassbler engine based on Zydis.

Parameters
BufferToDisassembleCurrent Bytes of assembly
BuffLengthLength of buffer
Isx86_64Whether it's an x86 or x64
Lengthof call (if return value is TRUE)
Returns
UINT32
851 {
852  ZydisDecoder decoder;
853  ZydisFormatter formatter;
854  UINT64 CurrentRip = 0;
855  int instr_decoded = 0;
856  ZydisDecodedInstruction instruction;
857  char buffer[256];
858  UINT32 MaximumInstrDecoded = 1;
859 
860  if (ZydisGetVersion() != ZYDIS_VERSION)
861  {
862  ShowMessages("invalid zydis version\n");
863  return DEBUGGER_CONDITIONAL_JUMP_STATUS_ERROR;
864  }
865 
866  if (Isx86_64)
867  {
868  ZydisDecoderInit(&decoder, ZYDIS_MACHINE_MODE_LONG_64, ZYDIS_ADDRESS_WIDTH_64);
869  }
870  else
871  {
872  ZydisDecoderInit(&decoder, ZYDIS_MACHINE_MODE_LONG_COMPAT_32, ZYDIS_ADDRESS_WIDTH_32);
873  }
874 
875  ZydisFormatterInit(&formatter, ZYDIS_FORMATTER_STYLE_INTEL);
876 
877  ZydisFormatterSetProperty(&formatter, ZYDIS_FORMATTER_PROP_FORCE_SEGMENT, ZYAN_TRUE);
878  ZydisFormatterSetProperty(&formatter, ZYDIS_FORMATTER_PROP_FORCE_SIZE, ZYAN_TRUE);
879 
880  //
881  // Replace the `ZYDIS_FORMATTER_FUNC_PRINT_ADDRESS_ABS` function that
882  // formats the absolute addresses
883  //
884  default_print_address_absolute =
885  (ZydisFormatterFunc)&ZydisFormatterPrintAddressAbsolute;
886  ZydisFormatterSetHook(&formatter, ZYDIS_FORMATTER_FUNC_PRINT_ADDRESS_ABS, (const void **)&default_print_address_absolute);
887 
888  while (ZYAN_SUCCESS(ZydisDecoderDecodeBuffer(&decoder, BufferToDisassemble, BuffLength, &instruction)))
889  {
890  //
891  // We have to pass a `runtime_address` different to
892  // `ZYDIS_RUNTIME_ADDRESS_NONE` to enable printing of absolute addresses
893  //
894  ZydisFormatterFormatInstruction(&formatter, &instruction, &buffer[0], sizeof(buffer), (ZyanU64)CurrentRip);
895 
896  //
897  // Return len of buffer
898  //
899  return instruction.length;
900  }
901 
902  //
903  // Error in disassembling buffer
904  //
905  return 0;
906 }

)

56

58  !g_IsSerialConnectedToRemoteDebugger)
59  {
60  va_start(Args, Fmt);

74  {

◆ g_DeviceHandle

HANDLE g_DeviceHandle
extern

Holds the global handle of device which is used to send the request to the kernel by IOCTL, this handle is not used for IRP Pending of message tracing.
